Package: memorySafe
Title: Out-of-Memory Data with Memory-Safe Mode
Version: 0.1.0.9000
Author: Dany Mukesha
Maintainer: Dany Mukesha <danymukesha@gmail.com>
Description: A high-level interface for working with out-of-memory data using
    a familiar data.frame-like interface. Data is stored in a local SQLite
    database and operations are translated to SQL, so you never need to load
    the full dataset into RAM. A "memory-safe" mode can be enabled that warns
    or errors before large data is materialized in memory.
License: MIT + file LICENSE
Imports:
    RSQLite,
    DBI,
    rlang (>= 1.0.0),
    tibble,
    utils,
    stats
Suggests:
    dplyr,
    testthat (>= 3.0.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
Config/roxygen2/version: 8.0.0
